<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">I think I am a little confused over how the effect of a spell focus decreases over levels past cap.  In this case I am specifically looking at mana pres items.  I have a talisman of the elements which is 20% mana preservation,  level cap of 67,  decrease by 10% per level past cap.  Now I always figured this meant that on level 68 spells it was 10% mana pres and 0% on all levels above that.  I recently got a Elandars Malodorous Linen Shirt which is 15% mana pres (detrimental), level cap 70.  Since the greater focus is always supposed to fire I figured that on all detrimental spells level 68 and higher the elandars would fire yet when I cast higher level detrimental spells even up to level 69 (euphoria etc...)  I am seeing my talisman of the elements fire instead of the shirt.  Can anyone explain why this is?</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
<br />
<table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="name"><a name="99009"></a></span><span class="postdetails">#2:&nbsp;<font color=black><b></b> Author:&nbsp;<b>Xoshia</b>,&nbsp;</font></span><span class="postdetails"><font color=black></font></span>
<a href="viewtopic.php?p=99009#99009"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails"><font color=black>Posted: Mon Mar 14, 2005 12:30 am</font><span class="gen"><br>
</td></tr>
<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">your 20% mana pres would lose 10% of its effectiveness.
<br />

<br />
so you would get like 20% at 67 , 18% at 68 , 16% at 69 , 14% at 70
<br />

<br />
as a result of the 16% efect at level 69 spell , its still running better than your all range 15% focus.
<br />

<br />
your skirt will only do its job for lv 70 spells.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
